This work is a Path B, field-driven study that uses semantic segmentation as a testbed to analyze how CNN architectural design choices influence robustness under real-world image degradation, with controlled experiments and analysis-focused conclusions.

Path B (Field-driven research)
 └── Chosen field / task (e.g., semantic segmentation)
      └── Research lenses
           ├── Architecture comparison
